OL,6,FIn a personal impact statement, the
OL,7,Fvictim described how the incident has
OL,8,Fchanged her life.
OL,10,FShe said: "I cannot explain to you the
OL,11,Ffeelings I experienced when I returned
OL,12,Fhome on that day and discovered my
OL,13,Fhouse had been broken into.
OL,15,F"There was the horror and heartbreak
OL,16,Fof opening each door to see it had
OL,17,Fbeen searched and noticing sentimental
OL,18,Fitems missing, praying that they had
OL,19,Fnot been taken and I would later find
OL,20,Fthem. I heavy heartedly knew this was
OL,21,Fwishful thinking.
