OL,6,F"I owe a huge debt of gratitude to the
OL,7,Fpolice who have been efficient and
OL,8,Fvery supportive. Without them, this
OL,9,Fwhole affair would have been very much
OL,10,Fharder to deal with."
OL,12,FPolice officers were able to seize
OL,13,Fsome of the stolen items from
OL,14,FHernandez's address in Southampton.
OL,16,FDet Sgt Ted Roe said: "Burglary is a
OL,17,Fcompletely invasive crime ` by doing
OL,18,Fwhat he did, Hernandez has left this
OL,19,Flady feeling extremely vulnerable and
OL,20,Fanxious in the one place she should
OL,21,Ffeel most safe.
